Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Perugia's limia (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that dominant males of Perugia's limia (species pictured) may be so preoccupied with fighting each other that the females end up mating with the subordinate males?

entry.title: Sophie Kropotkin (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Sophie Kropotkin and her husband returned to France despite the risk of being arrested, as they thought that detention in a French prison would be preferable to living in England?

entry.title: Guess (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that following the filming of the music video for "Guess", Charli XCX and Billie Eilish donated 10,000 pairs of underwear to charity?

entry.title: Winzar Kakiouea (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Winzar Kakiouea was the sole athlete from his nation at the 2024 Olympics?

entry.title: 1988 White Mountain Fire (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that resources to fight the 1988 White Mountain Fire were slow to arrive because of fires at Yellowstone?

entry.title: Jules Loh (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that journalist Jules Loh reported that Malcolm X told him that "his own people would kill him" before his assassination?

entry.title: Bangué (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Bangué, the smallest island of the Bazaruto Archipelago, was formed by ocean waves shaped by the surrounding archipelago?

entry.title: Ohio State University's TV station (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that The Game led to a boom in all-channel TV sales so viewers could see the game on Ohio State University's TV station?

entry.title: Drukqs (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Aphex Twin never intended to release Drukqs and only did so because he accidentally left an MP3 player on a plane?
